  "title": "Admin Coordinator (Singapore-Mexico)",
  "description": "<p>The Administrative Coordinator will be based in Singapore and provide administrative, operational, and basic accounting support for both Singapore and Mexico operations. This role requires strong organizational skills, attention to detail, and the flexibility to travel to Mexico when necessary to support office setup and coordination activities.</p><p><u><strong>Administrative Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li><p>Manage daily office operations in Singapore, including maintenance, office supplies, equipment, and general administrative functions to ensure smooth workflow</p></li><li><p>Handle correspondence, phone calls, and email communications on behalf of management</p></li><li><p>Prepare, organize, and maintain documents, reports, presentations, and meeting materials</p></li><li><p>Maintain and update company records, files, databases, and administrative systems</p></li><li><p>Support overseas office setup, coordination, and vendor management, particularly for the Mexico office</p></li><li><p>Perform other ad-hoc administrative duties as assigned</p></li></ul><p><u><strong>Travel & Coordination</strong></u></p><p><ul><li>Arrange business travel including flight bookings, visa applications, accommodation, and transportation</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Travel to Mexico when required to support administrative setup needs</li></ul></p><ul><li>Prepare and process travel expense claims and reimbursement reports</li></ul><p><u><strong>Basic Accounting & Finance Support</strong></u></p><p><ul><li>Prepare basic invoices and assist in tracking payments and outstanding balances</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Manage petty cash, expense tracking, and simple reconciliations</li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Assist the finance team with receipt collection, scanning, filing, and documentation</li></ul><p><br /><br />Minimum 2 years of administrative or coordination experience preferred.</p></p><p>• Excellent organizational and multitasking skills.</p><p>• Strong attention to detail and ability to work independently.</p><p>• Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)</p><p>• Good communication skills, both written and verbal.</p><p>• Willingness to travel overseas for work assignments (e.g., Mexico).</p>",
